                                        </a>
                                    </small>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="mask">&nbsp;</div>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

        <div class="download-content">
            <div class="installation-help">
                <p><a href="#" class="installation-help-reveal">
                    <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right"></span>
                    Primeiro, <em>instale o instlador de symfony</em>. Depois, execute este comando:
                </a></p>
                <div class="installation-help-content">
                    <p>
                        The <strong>Symfony Installer</strong> is a small PHP application that
                        must be installed once in your computer. It greatly simplifies
                        the creation of new projects based on the Symfony framework.
                    </p>

                    <h5>Installation on Linux and Mac OS X</h5>
                    <div class="console">
                        <div class="command">
                            $ sudo curl -LsS https://symfony.com/installer -o /usr/local/bin/symfony<br>
                            $ sudo chmod a+x /usr/local/bin/symfony
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h5>Installation on Windows</h5>
                    <div class="console">
                        <div class="command">
                            c:\&gt; php -r "file_put_contents('symfony', file_get_contents('https://symfony.com/installer'));"
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Move the downloaded file to your projects directory and
                        execute it as <code>php symfony</code>.
                    </p>

                    <div class="box box-secondary">
                        <p>
                            <strong>If you can't use the installer</strong> try instead the
                            <a href="http://symfony.com/doc/master/book/installation.html#creating-symfony-applications-without-the-installer">Symfony installation based on Composer</a>.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tab-content">
                <div id="version-stable" class="console tab-pane fade in active">
                    <div class="command clearfix">
                        $ <span class="text-to-copy">symfony new my_project</span>
                        <button class="hidden-xs btn btn-copy pull-right hidden">
                            <span class="icon-clipboard"></span>
                            Copiar
                        </button>
                    </div>

                    <div class="third-party-services">
                        <div class="service">
                            <img class="icon" src="{{ asset('bundles/app/img/icon-platformsh.png') }}">
                            <a
                                class="download-partner"
                                data-partner="platformsh"
                                data-type="framework"
                                href="https://accounts.platform.sh/platform/trial/symfony/setup?branch=3.0">
                                Deploy com Platform.sh
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="version-lts" class="console tab-pane fade">
                    <div class="command clearfix">
                        $ <span class="text-to-copy">symfony new my_project 2.8</span>
                        <button class="hidden-xs btn btn-copy pull-right hidden">
                            <span class="icon-clipboard"></span>
                            Copiar
                        </button>
                    </div>

                    <div class="third-party-services">
                        <div class="service">
                            <img class="icon" src="{{ asset('bundles/app/img/icon-platformsh.png') }}">
                            <a class="download-partner" data-partner="platformsh" data-type="framework" href="https://accounts.platform.sh/platform/trial/symfony/setup?branch=2.8">Deploy to Platform.sh</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="download-more">
        <div class="row">
            <div id="download-demo-application" class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="download-more-item">
                    <img src="{{ asset('bundles/app/img/demoapp.svg') }}">
                    <h4>Symfony Demo</h4>
                        <p>
                            A melhor maneira de aprender codigo Symfony e a referência para
                            desenvolver aplicações seguindo as melhores práticas oficiais.
                        </p>


                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-6 preferred">
                            <a href="https://github.com/symfony/symfony-demo">Download</a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm-6 third-party-service">
                            <img class="icon" src="{{ asset('bundles/app/img/icon-platformsh.png') }}">
                            <a class="download-partner" data-partner="platformsh" data-type="demo" href="https://accounts.platform.sh/platform/trial/symfony/setup?branch=demo">Deploy com Platform.sh</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="download-more-item">
                    <img src="{{ asset('bundles/app/img/subscribe.svg') }}">
                    <h4>Não perca nenhuma atualização!</h4>
                    <p>
                        Receba um email quando uma nova versão de Symfony seja
                        publicada ou quando uma versão esteja prestes a expirar.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <a href="{{ path('roadmap') }}">Suscriba gratis</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="download-components">
        <h2>Como utilizar os <br> componentes de Symfony</h2>
        <p>
            O framework de Symfony foi contruido sobre um conjunto de componentes
            PHP independentes e reusáveis chamado de <a href="http://symfony.com/components">
            <strong>Componentes de Symfony</strong></a>. Este conjunto esta se tornando
            a base padrão sobre a qual as melhores aplicações PHP são contruidas. Você
            pode utiliza-los nas suas aplicações web independente de usar Symfony ou não.
        </p>


        <div class="download-content">
            <div class="download-content-components">
                <p>Adicionar Componentes de Symfony à sua aplicação web:</p>

                <div class="console">
